# Website deploy workflow

When you change anything under `apps/website/` (HTML, CSS, assets):

1. **Finish the edit** — keep pages static; no build step required.
2. **Publish to `hardiktiwari/tandem-site` only** — clone or pull that repo, copy changed files from `apps/website/`, commit, and push to `main`.
3. **Do not deploy via `Sach1ng/tandem`** — ignore `sach1ng.github.io/tandem` and do not push website-only changes to the monorepo for Pages.
4. **Share the live URL** — https://hardiktiwari.github.io/tandem-site/ (or `…/roadmap.html` etc.)

Do not leave website work local-only. Preview with `npm run roadmap:open` or a local server, but always push to `hardiktiwari/tandem-site` when done.

If the user asked not to commit in the same message, finish the edit and remind them the site still needs a push to `hardiktiwari/tandem-site`.
